  <div class="views-field views-field-nothing-1">        <span class="field-content"><h4 class="latest-news-item-title dark-heading text-center text-bold"><a href="/blog/2020/11/it%E2%80%99s-complicated-six-things-worth-discussing-about-free-speech">It’s Complicated: Six Things Worth Discussing About Free Speech</a><br>
  <small>November 18, 2020 by <a href="/people/ivor-shapiro">Ivor Shapiro</a></small>
</h4>
<div class="margin-top-sm">
  <span class="latest-news-author-image"><a href="/people/ivor-shapiro"><img typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-responsive" src="https://cfe.ryerson.ca/sites/default/files/styles/100x100_sc/public/IvorShapiro.jpg?itok=dx_uKgay" width="100" height="100" alt="" /></a></span>
  <p>Well, hello again. Having ended <a href="https://cfe.ryerson.ca/blog/2020/10/dangerous-dialogues-how-speaking-freely-changes-lives-and-sometimes-ends-them">last month's column</a> with a candid appeal for readers to "talk back" about free speech, I was grateful to those who took me at my word. They made me think new thoughts, which is, of course, the whole idea.</p>

</div>

<p class="text-center margin-top"><a class="btn btn-default btn-brand btn-brand-transparent text-bold-upper" href="/blog/2020/11/it%E2%80%99s-complicated-six-things-worth-discussing-about-free-speech">Read More</a></p>

<hr class="visible-xs"></span>  </div>  </div>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
