  <div class="views-field views-field-nothing">        <span class="field-content"></span>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-nothing-1">        <span class="field-content"><h4 class="latest-news-item-title dark-heading text-center text-bold"><a href="/news/meghan-mcdermott-joins-cfe-board">Meghan McDermott Joins CFE Board</a><br>
  <small>November 3, 2020</small>
</h4>
<div class="margin-top-sm">
  <span class="latest-news-custom-image"></span>
  <p><a href="https://cfe.ryerson.ca/people/meghan-mcdermott">Meghan McDermott</a>, interim policy director for the British Columbia Civil Liberties Association, is joining the Centre for Free Expression Advisory Board. Meghan has a B.A. in philosophy from Concordia University, a J.D. from the University of Victoria, and LL.M. from the University of Edinburgh where her work focused on whether parties to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change have a responsibility to share the benefits of their forestry-related activities with local and Indigenous communities. </p>
</div>

<p class="text-center margin-top"><a class="btn btn-default btn-brand btn-brand-transparent text-bold-upper" href="/news/meghan-mcdermott-joins-cfe-board">Read More</a></p></span>  </div>  </div>
